Results.ReviewText:
The first thing that always hits me on opening a new jar of Nescafe Gold Blend is the aroma, which isn't flat and slightly stale like many cheaper instant coffees. Instead it is a warm, rich aroma very like it smells after adding water and this doesn't fade with time. It smells the same at the end of the jar as it does at the start. 
The taste is rounded and smooth- I'm not a fan of bitter, hard edged coffees so for me this is perfect served with good splash of milk. Nescafe Gold Blend is more expensive than some brands but the quality makes it worth the extra money especially as there are often discounts at the bigger supermarkets and with environmentally friendly, refillable options available too it is even better value. A classic and still the best!
